hopobject.body: It's funny goodluck mg orgazen A job applicant can explain long spells of unemployment in a job interview with a careful and convincing story about training, family obligations, or just plain bad luck, hoping that his other virtues would more than compensate. But the spread of employment screening software makes it hard even get to the interview, and lying is risky since online background checks have elevated the odds and consequences of getting caught.
